The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | For Americans, India sixth most popular country
                                                                                                               For Americans, India sixth most popular country
                            
	Washington, March 11 (PTI): India is the sixth most popular country in the US, with 69 per cent Americans having a positive view of the nation, according to a poll. Pakistan is among the 10 most unpopular nations.         
	Of 22 countries rated in the Gallup 2008 world affairs survey, Canada, Great Britain, Germany and Japan were favoured by 80 per cent Americans. The top four were followed by Israel at 71 per cent.        
	India tied with France at the sixth spot. Pakistan was viewed favourably by 22 per cent and negatively by 72 per cent.        
	The survey showed 73 per cent perceived Afghanistan negatively, 77 per cent Iraq and 88 per cent Iran.        
	About six in 10 Americans had a favourable view of Egypt, South Korea and Mexico, Gallup USA said.        
	Ten countries were viewed unfavourably by at least half the Americans. Of these, Iran, North Korea, the Palestinian authority, Iraq, Afghanistan, Pakistan, and Cuba were viewed more negatively than positively.                                                                                                                                                                            
